SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c03757330
Version: 1

HPSBHF02878 rev.1 - HP Smart Zero Client, Unauthorized Access

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2013-06-24
Last Updated: 2013-06-24

Potential Security Impact: Unauthorized access

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with the HP Smart Zero
Client. This vulnerability could be exploited by a local user on the device
to gain unauthorized access.

References: CVE-2013-2339 (SSRT101198)

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP Smart Zero Core v4.3 and v4.3.1 running on:
HP t5565z Smart Client
HP t410, All-in-One Smart Zero Client
HP t410 Smart Zero Client
HP t510 Flexible Thin Client
HP t610 Flexible Thin Client
HP t610 PLUS Flexible Thin Client

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2013-2339    (AV:L/AC:L/Au:N/C:P/I:P/A:P)       4.6
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

HP has provided updated operating system software for HP Smart Zero Core OS
v4.3 and v4.3.1. Please choose one of three methods below to resolve the
issue on the thin client.

Issue can be solved by one of three update methods, available from hp.com .

Select 'Support & Drivers'
Enter the specific model that is affected such as t410, t510, or t610
Select the model
Select HP Smart Client Choose one of two updates that resolve the
vulnerability:
Select and install Citrix Login Fix v3.13-1-1 on Smart Zero Core OS v4.3 or
v4.3.1
Download and install Smart Zero Core Image v4.3.2

